The sky that I see today, the hues that reflect upon my existence haven’t just shown up in a fortnight out of nowhere but has amounted through everything that went into dreaming and seeing it happen before it did. Sometimes, you focus not just on what could be done with piece later on, but on how much your life connects with why you make something happen. 

The conquest of streaking through the rocks, scaling the mountains that never were visible yet always existed in the dreamline, that’s what this Sunrise is all about. 

Giving back love to the world and for having me here amongst some of the brightest stars ✨

It’s not very often that you get to walk through your life in an imaginary sense just to recall what you’ve dreamt of many years ago only to see it all come together while you deeply are rooted to it all being God’s plan. 

One man who’s changed many things for many people around him, including myself, in a way where good things cumulatively pack up a lifelong present. For many years now, I’ve only known of him as a superstar but over the last couple of months of working with the man himself, in a very close and vulnerable relationship, I became a bigger fan of not just the performer he is, but how amazing of a human one could be. Haven’t met someone so humble, calm and charming in his own right, Ram Charan isn’t just a name but an emotion that prevails among millions of his fans that value him for how he adds up to each life. 

Thank you for everything, Sir. Grateful to life to have brought our vision, love for art together. Wishing you the best of many birthdays and a life full of happiness 💫❤️ @alwaysramcharan 

Shot by @arifminhaz

Ten years ago right around those toddler years, I happened to get visually introduced to this lil goofball called Harsha through a short film Viva which blew up crazy and changed the entire comic short film scene down south. Ever since, this main character energy called Viva Harsha has been making waves and the tides have surmounted to a banger like no-one’s expected.  Fast forward, here we are and I can’t be happier for this one amazing human. ( truth be told, this write-up has been on my mind for a really long time and it aligns so much with how things have shot up and drove my life for as long years as well ). Harsha, you’re one amazing human and if there’s anything that’s gotten you this far and shall open many more miraculous doors for you is your Hard Work and your spirit of kindness, morality and being human besides your undying passion for films. 
Put aside the brotherhood, from the bottom of my heart - you will always be our beloved Sundaram Master, our loving Harsha and life’s only getting better going forward. ✨❤️

Can’t wait to unlock magic, experience life together and make art that lives for gazillion years and beyond. ♥️😇

Every waking day in your presence is another blessing in disguise. ♥️

Through the journey of being this badass Sivagami to now my lil puppy who’s smile is enough to make any moment a wonderful one, I wish you nothing but peace at heart, happiness in life and knowing you’ll always be in safe hands with Gugu, Kuku and myself around. 

Thank you for doing everything you could to give us this wonderful life and provide for us through all these years. 

You’re my Hero and will always be the one I love. 🧿🌎

~ Gundamma’s Kanna 

( the third picture is from her last outing with her Grandson when she was in a state to walk and move around, picture shot many years ago)

Clock’s ticking, pages flipping. A deep voice in my head that wants me to hear what’s unsaid, undermining what the calmness and eternal values that the character holds. Maybe it’s supposed to rise to a different hue at dawn or maybe you wait for it to set off in a way you haven’t expected for it to set off at dusk- either ways there’s an untold tale, a tale that only you know and can never be mentally cloned for how you experience it. 

Maybe this is what life holds, so grip tight and save yourself from what hasn’t occurred through the plan and pray for the window the higher power wants you to look through. Fear isn’t permanent too. Maybe it’s the universe’s calling and it’s time to realise what’s unwinding in front of you. ✨

With and for @natgeotravel

Congratulations on bagging the National Film Award for Best Actor for one banger of a performance in Pushpa. Kudos to Sir @aryasukku and the entire team of #pushpa 🤍🤍

A special post for one person who’s been riding along, being the best wingman one can ever be.  Thank you for reading life couple of steps ahead than I do, making sure things are as perfect as they can be at any given point.  Thank you for taking care of me both on and off set and transcending to become the person I spend the most time with, ruffing through my Ted talks and wading through tough times together. 

Most of what you see up here on @arifminhaz has many steps put together, lot of which is to be credited to @thejaswitanneru for making my life easy. From being the first long term full-time assistant to a part time babysitter on the side whilst managing jobs all by herself- jobs that’d take multiple people on board to monitor and to make sure it’s all on point. 

As we coast off to different horizons and working from a very new scape, I wish you great success and shall forever hold gratitude for everything you’ve done and been. 

#grateful

From having an entire month’s time to plan surprises to I come see you right out of a FaceTime call after years of living away from you to now wishing I get to see you on your birthday either before you’re off for work or before you get to bed, life has become a 180 clock block. 

Although living under the same roof yet getting to see you no more than once a week, just waiting for those one-minute momma bear hugs keeps everything together in my life. 

It’s a shame that the only time I make for us is to text back about dinner or a “ love you “ message once in a while but I know life isn’t going to be like this forever. 

I know it’s your prayers that save me on the cruelest of days and I know it’s your thoughts that have me latch a purpose to life.  Thank you for never giving up on me mom, thank you for working so hard for me and thank you for being my Hero that has always fought and continues to fight many battles that are unknown to the world. 

Happy Birthday to you Gugu 🌍 
2nd October 2023. 

( Picture from 2020, I hope to have a picture together on each of our birthdays going forward )

Three days ago, looming from darkness to a will that existed for life - I lost my best friend’s dad to cancer.  One day that ripped the aid called “ hope “, a suffering that could only be experienced by none but the one that battled it with a heart that beat to live another day with a purpose filled with love and compassion. 

Venugopal uncle was such a charming man, kind hearted and cared for everyone dearly. He’s had the most amazingly thick, super iconic hair, a wonderful smile and his quest to know what I was upto with my photographic explorations filled my heart. 

He loved his son’s best friends like his own. From being a father figure since schooling - to also sharing a son-father silence and awkwardness whilst conversations whenever I was at Ashay’s to pick him up, he was nothing less than someone I looked up to as a father. 

Malayalam is something I never spoke but his smile and the eyes that sparkled with sense of pride conveyed enough emotions for me to know how highly he spoke of me to everyone who knew his son, the realisation struck way before experiencing how everyone knew me at his funeral. 

You’ve raised an amazing boy, uncle.  Someone Sreejith and I consider ourselves blessed to be sharing this life with. We’ve seen the battles that Ashay and aunty had to fight over the last year and a half, imaginations put very far away from soaking in how you’ve fought each day and believed it shall pass. 

The day has come and god has put an end to your suffering. While “ Acchan “ echoes in my head just the way Ashay was asked to call you thrice before you were put to rest, I’m sure you are proud of the man that held the ends of the cross together and fought along - Ashay is and shall become a man like you and hold people close to heart just the way you did. 

Always in our heart. Now and forever. 🤍

The brightest star, a promising soul. 💫

Been just about a month since I swooshed out, took over a week for me to tap into senses to feel what it’s like to be stepping into 2024. There are emotions that can only be experienced, moments that can only be lived and thoughts that can only be switched, drive that can only be ignited when you rough through an entire year of uncertainties, opportunities, downfalls, neutralities, days you realise what’s worth and not of your time, presence and effort, and beyond all - keeping the people that love you close to your heart.  All I have is gratitude, love for god, my family and each one of you that have contributed to my learning, growth and evolving into a better human than before. 

Cannot wait to unfold what’s in store for 2024, lovely humans that I’d be getting to share my thoughts and experiences of life with, amazing creatives that I’d be working with and I hope we all get closer to our dreams, desires and everything that we wish and pray for. ♥️🌍
